2
00:00:04,216 --> 00:00:07,372
 ¢Ü Happy birthday to you ¢Ü

3
00:00:07,372 --> 00:00:11,353
 ¢Ü Happy birthday, dear Roween ¢Ü

4
00:00:11,353 --> 00:00:14,916
 ¢Ü Happy birthday to you ¢Ü

5
00:00:14,916 --> 00:00:20,653
Aw, geez. What a beautiful cake.
Could've done without the candles, though.

6
00:00:20,653 --> 00:00:24,433
Oh, Baloney. When you were a kid, 
you couldn't wait to blow out the candles.

7
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:26,710
Yeah, back then,
there weren't 30 of them.

8
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:29,369
Oh, go on, Ro, make a wish.

9
00:00:33,395 --> 00:00:35,334
Go, go, go, go!

10
00:00:37,857 --> 00:00:39,091
What did you wish for?

11
00:00:39,091 --> 00:00:41,256
I can't say,
or it won't come true.

12
00:00:41,256 --> 00:00:44,008
Oh, look who likes being the kid now.

13
00:00:44,008 --> 00:00:45,863
Okay, but don't laugh.

14
00:00:47,246 --> 00:00:49,151
I wished I'd win the lotto.

15
00:00:49,151 --> 00:00:51,240
Then I could take a cruise,

16
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:55,313
go on safari, travel to Greece,
travel the world.

17
00:00:58,004 --> 00:01:01,994
I think your wish was perfect, Ro.
And now...

18
00:01:02,307 --> 00:01:05,320
you'll be ready for anything.

19
00:01:05,320 --> 00:01:07,299
Oh, Terri.

20
00:01:12,015 --> 00:01:14,301
And don't you dare say they aren't you.

21
00:01:14,301 --> 00:01:15,679
You can't afford these.

22
00:01:15,679 --> 00:01:17,842
Oh, the store gives me half-off.

23
00:01:20,930 --> 00:01:22,757
Sorry, Ro, I do have to run.

24
00:01:23,605 --> 00:01:25,893
You sure you don't want to come out?

25
00:01:26,887 --> 00:01:28,393
You're sweet, I can't.

26
00:01:28,393 --> 00:01:31,420
Tomorrow I have to be 
at work first thing.

27
00:01:41,297 --> 00:01:42,831
Go!

28
00:01:43,243 --> 00:01:44,779
Let me see your hands!

29
00:01:44,779 --> 00:01:48,798
Back away from the alarms!
Go! Do it now!

30
00:01:49,181 --> 00:01:51,703
You, get down on the ground!

31
00:02:33,007 --> 00:02:34,920
Got something off the teletype.

32
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:37,176
Robbery at Emerson bank
this morning, southeast branch.

33
00:02:37,176 --> 00:02:40,000
- Big heist?
- All told, $300,000.

34
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,850
Robbery have something to do
with a homicide?

35
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:43,820
Nick and I caught a case six years back.

36
00:02:43,820 --> 00:02:46,319
Lady teller was killed during a holdup.

37
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:47,844
Same branch.

38
00:02:47,844 --> 00:02:50,762
Bank getting hit twice
makes it the same crew?

39
00:02:50,762 --> 00:02:54,433
Well, these guys were wearing Johnny 
Cash masks, just like six years ago.

40
00:02:54,433 --> 00:02:57,729
Plus, this crew was armed with sawed-off 
pump-action shotguns, same as last time.

41
00:02:57,729 --> 00:03:00,904
So catch who took down today's score,
and we put down your old case.

42
00:03:00,904 --> 00:03:05,415
If I remember right, the victim was a real 
wallflower type, minding her own business.

43
00:03:05,415 --> 00:03:08,504
Right. Wrong place, wrong time.

44
00:03:08,504 --> 00:03:13,471
Sad./ Soon as they shot her, 
armed robbery became murder one.

45
00:03:13,471 --> 00:03:15,324
There you are.

46
00:03:15,324 --> 00:03:16,424
Hey, you been looking for me?

47
00:03:16,424 --> 00:03:20,253
- Not me, uh, some dude on a Harley.
- Oh?

48
00:03:20,253 --> 00:03:23,257
Yeah, Ray something-or-other.

49
00:03:25,212 --> 00:03:27,048
Well...

50
00:03:30,389 --> 00:03:32,772
It must be something personal.

51
00:03:34,859 --> 00:03:37,473
I'm just saying.

52
00:03:37,473 --> 00:03:40,069
Guy on a Harley, always sexy.

53
00:03:40,069 --> 00:03:43,449
Sure there's nothing
you want to share, Lil?

54
00:03:44,633 --> 00:03:49,129
Yeah. He shows up again,
tell him I'm dead.

